  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Dodge</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>physical.dodge</abilityid>
    <abilityclass>Reaction</abilityclass>
    <keywords><physical/></keywords>
    <abilityattrmodifiers><attr>Agility</attr><attr>Speed</attr></abilityattrmodifiers>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	After the character is hit and/or damage is rolled the character
	may use their standard action to attempt to dodge the attack.
	If successful the attack is dodged and the character takes no damage.
	Note that unlike most other reactions Dodging requires the character
	to spend their action!
      </p>

      <p>
	Some types of attack cannot be dodged, e.g. surprise attacks and
	poisonous gas attacks.  Other types of attack e.g. the acid or 
	fire attacks of dragons may be dodgeable depending on the context
	and deal half or no damage (at the GM's discretion).
      </p>

      <p>
	Once the character fails a dodge they are rattled and can no longer
	dodge for the rest of that combat.
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>

    <abilitylevels>
      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>0</levelnumber>
        <prereqabilitylevel></prereqabilitylevel>
        <successes>5</successes>
        <check>Std 2d8 vs DDC 14</check>
