    <keywords><physical/></keywords>
    <abilityattrmodifiers><attr>Strength</attr><attr>Endurance</attr></abilityattrmodifiers>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	Grappling involves grabbing, tackling or wrestling an opponent and holding 
	them without harming them.  Other attacks against a grappled opponent
	are hindered by the grappler being close to the opponent and the opponents
	struggling.
      </p>

      <p>
	Every round that an opponent is grappled they may make an opposed Str test 
	against their grappler to escape.  Once grappled it takes a round for 
	a second character to tie-up, or otherwise constrain, the opponent.
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>

